# Heart-Disease-Prediction
# 🩺 Heart Disease Prediction - ML Mini Project
# -------------------------------------------------------
# 🔧 Model       : Logistic Regression
# 📁 Dataset     : heartData.csv
# 🎯 Goal        : Predict if a person has heart disease
# 🧠 Input       : Clinical attributes (e.g., age, cholesterol)
# 📊 Output      : 0 = Healthy Heart | 1 = Defective Heart
# ✅ Status      : Completed

# -------------------------------------------------------
# 📌 Workflow Summary:
# -------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Imported necessary libraries
# 2. Loaded the dataset and checked for missing values
# 3. Explored target distribution (Healthy vs Defective)
# 4. Separated features (x) and target (y)
# 5. Split the data into training and test sets (80/20)
# 6. Trained Logistic Regression model
# 7. Evaluated model on both training and test data
# 8. Built a prediction system for new input

# -------------------------------------------------------
# 📈 Performance:
# -------------------------------------------------------
# 🧪 Training Accuracy : ~84%
# 🧾 Testing Accuracy  : ~91%
# Model performs decently with logistic regression

# -------------------------------------------------------
# 📦 Requirements:
# -------------------------------------------------------
# pip install pandas numpy scikit-learn

# -------------------------------------------------------
# 🧠 Model Notes:
# -------------------------------------------------------
# • Logistic Regression was used as it's simple and effective
# • You can experiment with RandomForestClassifier, SVM, etc.
# • Later convert this to a Streamlit app for interactivity
